.SH NAME
task3 \- Process manager for listing and signaling processes
.SH SYNOPSIS
task3
.SH DESCRIPTION
The Process Manager provides:
.IP \[bu] 2
List all processes (independent of terminal)
.IP \[bu] 2
List processes grouped by user
.IP \[bu] 2
Display PIDs of all processes
.IP \[bu] 2
Run or stop a specific process
.IP \[bu] 2
Send specific signals to a process
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B List all processes
Shows PID, user, command, state, and elapsed time.
.TP
.B List by user
Filters processes by the specified username.
.TP
.B Show all PIDs
Displays only process IDs.
.TP
.B Run a process
Starts a command and reports its PID.
.TP
.B Stop a process
Sends SIGSTOP to the given PID.
.TP
.B Send a signal
Sends a chosen signal number (e.g., 15 SIGTERM, 9 SIGKILL) to the PID.
